Seven-Up Cos, a unit of Philip MorrisCos Inc, is raising 155.78 mln dlrs via an offering of seniorsubordinated notes due 1997 yielding 12-1/8 pct, said leadunderwriter Donaldson, Lufkin and Jenrette Securities Corp.    The notes have a 7-1/2 pct coupon and were priced at 89.87.    Non-callable for three years, the debt is rated B-3 byMoody's Investors Service Inc and CCC-plus by Standard andPoor's Corp.  The issue was raised from an initial offering of140 mln dlrs. Reuter&#3;